About Me

I am a freelance Wordpress and front-end developer residing in Asheville, North Carolina with my husband, dog, 2 cats, and 4 chickens (for you animal lovers, pictures are below). Originally from Pennsylvania, we moved here about three years ago after falling in the love with the mountains and culture of Western NC. I gained an interest coding (and the power behind Wordpress) when I built my first website, for my first entrepreneurial venture as a Virtual Research Assistant. At the time, I did not have experience in tech, but a Master's Degree in Sociology and years of experience as a Research Assistant. Over the next few years I worked as a Virtual Assistant, and part of my work often included helping clients to test, manage or update their websites. Among my clients, I saw a great need for a reliable, detail-oriented developer that didn't charge an exorbitant fee. Over this time, I developed my coding skills through various online programs (check them out here), and countless hours of hands-on practice. I’ve been specializing my learning in front-end development, WordPress, and responsive design. My HTML is validated and search engine optimized, my CSS is organized and uses industry standard best practices, and my WordPress sites are easily updated. Work is always delivered on-time or ahead of schedule, and I strive to answer all emails and calls within 24 hours (48 hours on the weekend). As someone who has managed websites and knows the frustration felt when something that should work doesn't, I always do my best to ensure that your website not only LOOKS great, but WORKS great too!

item.title: Services
item.dc:creator: LaGreen19
item.content:encoded:
Wordpress

Wordpress is a powerful content management system that allows for easy updating, and access to thousands of plug-ins that can be used to add almost any feature you want to your website. I offer fully custom build themes using the Underscores framework, fully customized websites using existing themes, and updates to existing Wordpress websites. I typically configure plug-ins such as Advanced Custom Fields (so that your website can be easily updated, by you), SEO by YOAST (so your website is Search Engine Optimized and people can more easily find your webiste), Contact Form 7 and Security plug-ins to prevent spam and hackers from messing with your website.  

Semantic, Validated HTML5 and CSS3

Having organized and fully commented code is important to keep on-going edits to your website under control, without confusion, slow load times. I work daily towards staying up to date with the latest standards and techniques. I build it all with care and attention to detail, cleanly designed for SEO, organized and commented so it is easy to modify and maintain.

Mobile Responsive Design

As the web is being viewed through an increasing number of devices, it’s more important than ever for businesses to have websites that are easily viewed from any device. I ensure that it is valid standards-compliant code that displays correctly in multiple web browsers, and across devices.

Ecommerce

Want your customers to be able to view and/or order your products online? I can configure your Wordpress website for this using WooCommerce, or I can build a simple storefront for you using Shopify.

Website Optimization

Google Analytics Configuration

This includes integrating your site with your Google Analytics account so you can gain valuable insists on how visitors are interacting with your site.

Social media configuration

New blog posts are automatically shared on your social media channels. Readers can easily share your material on social media, making it easier for new users to find your website.

Website Testing and Audits

Make sure your website is working as expected, all of your links work, and there are no issues between browsers or devices. I can audit your website and let you know areas for improvement.

Website Maintenance

Page Updates & Blog Formatting

You create the content and I’ll format it the way you want (and proofread it for you). I’ll even source high quality images to go with it and optimize it with the appropriate tags for SEO You’ll notice the difference the extra formatting touches with make to your blog presence.

Monthly maintenance package

On a monthly basis, I will make sure that your website is up-to-date and functioning as expected. This includes updating your version of Wordpress, updating plug-ins as needed, and makings sure that all of your links work and your website continues to look great. This also includes a monthly Google Analytics report, and a 30 minute consultation where I will review this report with you and we can touch base on any other updates are coming up.

Weekly blog support

On a weekly basis, I will add an SEO-optimized blog post to your website. You provide the content, and I can help you with proofreading, optimizing for SEO, finding, creating and adding pictures. I will then post the blog to your website, and on all of your social media channels. This package also includes a monthly 1 hour consultation and google analytics reporting.

item.title: About
item.dc:creator: LaGreen19
item.content:encoded:
A little about me and my coding journey:

I live in beautiful Asheville, NC with my husband, dog, 2 cats, and 4 chickens.  My carer in web development actually began when I was launching my freelance business as a Virtual Assistant and undertook that task of creating my own Wordpress website. While I enjoyed the process of making my own website, I did not realize that a career in web development was a feasible thing for me. With a master's degree in Sociology, and work experience primarily in the fields of research and administration, I didn't think that was a feasible career pivot to make. After working as a VA for a year or so, I realized that in the long run I was not going to be happy with the type of work I was finding. And the work I did enjoy typically involved tech - editing videos, setting up automated systems, updating Wordpress websites, etc. I began to research this as a possibility and found a plethora of online resources and support, and many stories of other people who had a background similar to mine that managed to learn to code and change their career. I began teaching myself to code with resources such as Free Code Camp and the Mozilla Developer Network. After wanting a little more structure, I enrolled in 2 Skillcrush Blueprints -- one for Front End Development and the other for Wordpress Development. Since starting this journey, I have developed a love for coding and creating beautiful websites.
